Network Technology

LTE

5 min read Glossary
Quick Definition

LTE (Long-Term Evolution) is an enhanced 4G network technology that delivers significantly faster download and upload speeds than earlier 2G and 3G networks. It provides typical speeds of 5-100 Mbps and remains the backbone of mobile connectivity worldwide.

Deep Dive

How This Applies to Vouch Mobile

Vouch Mobile provides full LTE coverage through AT&T's nationwide network. When you're in an area without 5G coverage, your phone automatically connects to AT&T's reliable 4G LTE network. With typical speeds of 5-100 Mbps, LTE handles everything from HD video streaming to video calls with ease. Plus, LTE uses less battery than 5G, helping extend your phone's battery life.
